smell_analysis.justification: All diagrams in the provided PDF appear to contain content and are not empty.

All use cases in the diagrams are either directly connected to an actor or connected via 'include' relationships to use cases that are connected to actors (e.g., 'Tuvasta kasutaja' and 'Vaata kõiki ootel...' are reachable).
No distinct use cases with synonymous names (e.g., 'Add Car' vs 'Register Car') associated with the same actor were found.
No instances of multiple model elements with the same name within the same package scope were definitively identified (different diagrams likely represent different views/packages).
No redundant data duplication found in tables. Shared column names like 'nimetus' appear to represent distinct attributes (e.g., Name of Car vs Name of Mark) or are Foreign Keys.
Use case naming is consistent, using the 'Verb Noun' pattern (e.g., 'Registreeri auto', 'Vaata kõiki autosid', 'Tuvasta kasutaja').
All states in the 'Auto seisundidiagramm' (Page 9) are reachable from the Start state.
All actions in the 'Auto lõpetamise tegevusdiagramm' (Page 4) are reachable via the control flow.
All visible relationships in class and database diagrams show multiplicity indicators at both ends.
No single diagram contains 10 or more central elements (classes, tables, use cases, or states). The maximum count observed was 9 tables on Page 15.
No single element was found with 6 or more visual connection lines on a specific diagram. The maximum observed was 5 lines (e.g., 'Isik' class on Page 6).
The layout of elements in the diagrams is generally compact and distances appear uniform.
All use cases and activity actions start with active verbs (e.g., 'Vaata', 'Otsi', 'Vali', 'Lõpeta').
No class, table, attribute, or use case names were found to be 3 characters or less. (e.g., 'Isik', 'Riik', 'Auto' are 4 characters).
Class names start with uppercase letters and are singular (e.g., 'Isik', 'Auto', 'Klient').
Attribute/column names start with lowercase letters (e.g., 'e_meil', 'reg_number', 'nimetus').
No type prefixes (like 'tbl_', 'str') were found in element names. Prefixes like 'PK_', 'FK_', 'IXFK_' are allowed exceptions.
